				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$p = \left( {\frac{k!}{{(n!\left( {n - k} \right)!}}} \right) \times pk \times \left( {1 - p} \right)\left( {n - k} \right) = \left( {\frac{k!}{{(n!\left( {n - k} \right)!}}} \right) \times 0.04k$$\end{document}p=k!(n!n-k!×pk×1-pn-k=k!(n!n-k!×0.04k

